         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>223, 344 n.3</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>69, 72</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... und auf Grund der Verbindung mit welchem [scil. dem Geist] der Überdruss "geistige Konzentration" genannt wird.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... and because of the connection to which [i.e. the spirit], weariness is called "spiritual concentration".</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>128</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Dies wird prāmodya genannt: Was dem, der den achtfachen Weg verwirklicht, daraus [wtl. deswegen] zu der Zeit [als] freudige Erregung [und] Sehnsucht entsteht, das wird prāmodya "Freude" genannt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">This is called prāmodya: [that] which develops in one who accomplishes the eightfold way therefore at that time [as] joyful excitement [and] longing, this is called prāmodya, "joy".</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>755</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>50, 63</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>94</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die für den Geist zum Sammeln der Tugenden die Grundlage bildende(?) Ursache an [seinem] Geschmeidigsein, die wird prasrabdhi "[innere] Ruhe" [wtl. das Entlassen [jeglicher Störung]] genannt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The reason for his being lissom, forming(?) the basis for the mind in the gathering of virtues, this is called prasrabdhi “[inner] calm” [lit. the release [of any disturbance]].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>224</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>220</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>20, 46, 42</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>92</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>642</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">‘[the mind] is disposed to gather virtues by the power of <hi>prasrabdhi</hi> [serenity] for the good morals. As <hi>kalyāṇa</hi> gold</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>737</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>220</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">As kalyāṇa gold is disposed to be worked if it is soft, so prasrabdhi [serenity] is to be understood.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>642</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">is disposed to be worked if it is soft, so <hi>prasrabdhi</hi> [serenity] is to be understood.’</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">avihiṃsā "Nichtverletzung". Das wird Nicht-verletzen genannt, vermöge dessen man andere nicht verletzt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">avihiṃsā "Non-injury". That is called non-injury, due to which one does not injure others.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>224</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1976"/><citedRange>229</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1976"/><citedRange>229</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>96</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
